# 🔧 ST22 — ABAP Dump Analysis

> ***SAP Basis Administration — Interview Preparation Guide***

---

## 📌 What is ST22?

**ST22** is a transaction code used to analyze ***ABAP runtime errors*** (commonly called **_short dumps_**).  
Whenever an ABAP program **terminates abnormally**, SAP generates a short dump and logs it in <ins>ST22</ins>.

> 💡 _Think of ST22 as the **crash report center** of your SAP system._

---

## 🎯 Purpose

- Displays **_detailed information_** about program crashes
- Shows the **error type**, the **_exact line of code_** that failed, the **user** who triggered it, the **timestamp**, and the **variable values** at the time of the dump
- Acts as the ***first point of investigation*** for any ABAP runtime failure

---

## 🔴 Common Dump Types _(Frequently Asked in Interviews)_

| Dump Type | Description | Severity |
|---|---|---|
| **`TIME_OUT`** | Program exceeded maximum runtime _(default: **600s** dialog, **3600s** background)_ | 🔴 _High_ |
| **`TSV_TNEW_PAGE_ALLOC_FAILED`** | Program ran out of memory _(extended memory / heap)_ | 🔴 _High_ |
| **`DBIF_RSQL_SQL_ERROR`** | Database-level **SQL error** occurred | 🔴 _High_ |
| **`MESSAGE_TYPE_X`** | Program hit a _hard termination_ via `MESSAGE TYPE X` | 🟡 _Medium_ |
| **`RABAX_STATE`** | Internal **_kernel-level_** error | 🔴 _High_ |
| **`COMPUTE_INT_ZERODIVIDE`** | Division by **zero** in ABAP code | 🟡 _Medium_ |
| **`CALL_FUNCTION_NOT_FOUND`** | Called function module **_does not exist_** | 🟡 _Medium_ |

---

## 📋 Information Provided by ST22

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| **Error Category** | Classification of the dump _(e.g., TIME_OUT, MEMORY, DB error)_ |
| **ABAP Program** | _Name of the program_ that crashed |
| **Source Code Line** | ***Exact line*** where the error occurred |
| **Call Stack** | Complete **_execution path_** leading to the crash |
| **User & Client** | The **SAP user** and **client number** who triggered it |
| **System & Host** | _Application server_ and **host machine** details |
| **Variable Values** | **_Snapshot_** of all variable values at the time of crash |
| **Error Analysis** | SAP's built-in ***suggestion*** on how to fix the issue |

---

## ⏳ Dump Retention Period

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **`rsdb/snp_lifetime`** | **_2 days_** | Profile parameter controlling dump retention |
| **`RSSNAPDL`** | ~~N/A~~ _(scheduled)_ | Reorganization report to **_clean up_** old dumps |

> ⚠️ _If you don't increase the retention, dumps older than **2 days** are <ins>automatically deleted</ins>._

